<center>
<p><font face="Arial Black"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>Navigational
Design</font></font></font></center>

<p><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>• An
application is seen as a navigational view over the conceptual model</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>•
Different navigational models may be built for the same conceptual schema
thus expressing different views on the same domain</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>•
Implement according to the corresponding user’s profile</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>•
Pre-defined types of navigational classes:</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Nodes</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Links</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Anchors</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Access structures</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+3>•
The navigational schema is similar to the previous one</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Built from classes(nodes and indexes) and relationships(links)</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Reflect the kind of navigation paths a particular kind of user may traverse</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
– Nodes and links may appear explicitly or not</font></font></font>
<br><font face="Times New Roman"><font color="#000000"><font size=+2></font></font></font>&nbsp;
